main event: An observer in Central Valley, California, reported seeing a white star-like object on May 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to climb and sometimes hovered in one spot., The observation lasted for about 2 minutes., The object disappeared while the observer was distracted and reappeared three times., Comparable to the brightness of a star, it was noted to be white in appearance., The observer had seen similar objects many times before.
witness description: Observer noted a white star-like object moving in the sky.
